ANNOUNCER OVER PA:
 Dr. Walker to Radiology.

30
00:02:07,795 --> 00:02:12,233
There isn't any word yet,
so get us some coffee,
this could be a long night.

31
00:02:12,266 --> 00:02:14,435
Oh, I don't think
you're allowed to smoke
those in here.

32
00:02:15,703 --> 00:02:18,472
Hey, didn't this happen
sometime before?

33
00:02:18,506 --> 00:02:19,840
You're thinking
of Len Bias.

34
00:02:19,873 --> 00:02:22,876
He OD'ed on coke
the night the ha was
drafted by the Celtics.

35
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,745
So you think this guy
was into drugs too?

36
00:02:25,713 --> 00:02:27,881
Drugs? Why drugs?

37
00:02:27,915 --> 00:02:29,217
'Cause he'a black, right?

38
00:02:29,250 --> 00:02:30,751
Okay, man. Take it easy.
Take it easy.

39
00:02:30,784 --> 00:02:33,321
Look, I didn't mean
any harm.

40
00:02:33,354 --> 00:02:34,755
Just leave us alone.
All right?

41
00:02:34,788 --> 00:02:35,889
Sorry, Bo.

42
00:02:41,895 --> 00:02:44,198
That young man is
Bo Kimble.

43
00:02:44,232 --> 00:02:46,200
He grew up with Gathers.

44
00:02:46,234 --> 00:02:48,936
They played on the same
team on high school.

45
00:02:48,969 --> 00:02:50,671
I would liked to have
interviewed him.

46
00:02:51,539 --> 00:02:52,673
Nice work.

47
00:02:54,942 --> 00:02:56,277
Sorry.

48
00:02:58,011 --> 00:03:00,448
Bank shouldn't have
been out there.

49
00:03:00,481 --> 00:03:02,950
I should've just flat refused
to play with him.

50
00:03:02,983 --> 00:03:06,820
Stop it, man. You know nobody
could keep Hank from playing.

51
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:09,823
I remember lots of times
Hank would have been
better staying off the court...

52
00:03:14,495 --> 00:03:15,929
[PEOPLE LAUGHING]

53
00:03:21,869 --> 00:03:23,203
BOY: I dare you to drive.

54
00:03:24,405 --> 00:03:25,706
Here, Hank.

55
00:03:27,641 --> 00:03:28,942
Yo, man, Hank.
You all right?

56
00:03:30,511 --> 00:03:32,380
You see how I
picked his pocket?

57
00:03:32,413 --> 00:03:33,847
Come on, man,
let's quit.

58
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:35,583
Scott Hardly, you give up?

59
00:03:36,584 --> 00:03:37,818
They're killing us.

60
00:03:37,851 --> 00:03:39,320
Come on. Let's play.

61
00:03:45,659 --> 00:03:48,296
Hank, you better come home.

62
00:03:48,796 --> 00:03:51,599
Derrick, watch this.

63
00:03:51,632 --> 00:03:53,501
I'll give these guys a facial.

64
00:03:54,535 --> 00:03:56,470
Big Loo, is looking for you.

65
00:03:57,471 --> 00:03:59,239
and she is not happy.

66
00:04:00,541 --> 00:04:03,243
Nice try, guys.
Better luck next time.

67
00:04:08,882 --> 00:04:12,886
Didn't you see the way me
and Heat were handling
those "Dudes".

68
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:15,022
Hank, they were creaming
you guys.

69
00:04:15,055 --> 00:04:17,024
And we showed them
a thing or two.

70
00:04:17,057 --> 00:04:19,927
Yeah, like how to get
your butt kicked.

71
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:23,030
Anyway, you were supposed to
be home to help mama Moo.

72
00:04:23,063 --> 00:04:25,065
She's gonna gawp on you, Hank.

73
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:27,267
Big Loo? Oh, hardly.

74
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:30,438
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:05:31,031 --> 00:05:34,768
I figure another four inches,
and I'll be able to palm.

76
00:05:34,802 --> 00:05:37,070
What if you're all
through growing, Hank?

77
00:05:37,104 --> 00:05:39,907
What if you're some kind
of freak of nature,

78
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:43,477
and you're the fattest kid
ever to stop growing at 11?

79
00:05:43,511 --> 00:05:45,546
Then you'll never be
able to palm the ball.

80
00:05:45,579 --> 00:05:46,947
I ain't through growing.

81
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:48,882
And what do you mean,
I ain't gonna be able
to palm the ball?

82
00:05:48,916 --> 00:05:50,083
You never know.

83
00:05:50,117 --> 00:05:52,486
I'm gonna grow.
And that's all
there is to it.

84
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:54,922
MAMA: So, how's everybody
doing in here?

85
00:05:55,456 --> 00:05:57,124
Hank?

86
00:05:57,157 --> 00:05:59,560
Did you finish
all your homework?

87
00:06:00,093 --> 00:06:01,495
You check.

88
00:06:01,529 --> 00:06:04,398
Honey, you think
I don't believe you?

89
00:06:04,432 --> 00:06:06,166
Give it here.
Let me see.
Give it here.

90
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:07,601
Let me see this.

91
00:06:08,469 --> 00:06:09,770
Mm-hm.

92
00:06:12,806 --> 00:06:14,408
Oh. [SIGHS]

93
00:06:15,142 --> 00:06:16,109
Oh!

94
00:06:16,143 --> 00:06:19,880
You know, I've prayed
long and hard for this.

95
00:06:19,913 --> 00:06:21,815
For Hank to do his homework?

96
00:06:21,849 --> 00:06:23,383
Oh, hush, dearie.

97
00:06:23,684 --> 00:06:25,285
No.

98
00:06:25,318 --> 00:06:30,090
No, for a nice clean home,
where my kids wouldn't have
to worry about drug dealers

99
00:06:30,123 --> 00:06:32,960
and thugs hanging around them
all the time.

100
00:06:32,993 --> 00:06:35,463
Mama, we just moved
down the street.

101
00:06:35,496 --> 00:06:37,465
It's not like we living
with the rich folks.

102
00:06:37,498 --> 00:06:39,900
Okay. So, we have a little
ways to go.

103
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:42,035
We'll get there.

104
00:06:42,069 --> 00:06:44,872
Yeah. As soon as I sign
with the Sixers

105
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:47,775
I'll buy the biggest house
there is.

106
00:06:47,808 --> 00:06:51,912
Oh, Hank, you make me happy
enough if you just keep up
with your school work, okay?

107
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:53,914
But in the mean time,

108
00:06:53,947 --> 00:06:57,150
when ya'll look out that window,
ya'll will see a tree.

109
00:07:00,187 --> 00:07:01,622
[BOTH LAUGH]

110
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:04,458
What tree?

111
00:07:05,559 --> 00:07:07,027
It's a great tree, mom.

112
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:10,631
Can make the all star team
for trees.

113
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:12,966
Thank you, Hank.

114
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,668
Good night, mama.
Good night.

115
00:07:14,702 --> 00:07:16,103
Good night, boy.
Good night.

116
00:07:16,136 --> 00:07:17,671
Okay, now you go to bed.

117
00:07:17,705 --> 00:07:18,806
Derrick, I'm telling you,

118
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:20,741
you wouldn't be able
to show these guys
how to play.

119
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:21,875
All right.
No question.

120
00:07:21,909 --> 00:07:23,511
You want me,
got it?

121
00:07:23,544 --> 00:07:26,046
Champion of the world,
and all of North Philly.

122
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,648
I'm telling you, man...

123
00:07:43,764 --> 00:07:45,599
I'm the doctor,

124
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:48,502
and this is
my house-call.

125
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:58,078
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

126
00:07:58,111 --> 00:07:59,613
Right over here.

127
00:08:02,049 --> 00:08:04,652
All right, welcome to
try-outs, gentlemen.

128
00:08:04,685 --> 00:08:07,621
Some of you may know,
my name is Father Dave.

129
00:08:07,655 --> 00:08:11,792
Now if you came here to play,
you came to the wrong place.

130
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:17,297
We don't play anything here.
That's what playgrounds are for.

131
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:22,202
This gym is for guys
who are willing to work,
and becoming a team.

132
00:08:24,638 --> 00:08:26,339
Now, line up on the base line.

133
00:08:26,373 --> 00:08:31,178
All I want each of you to do is
dribble the ball out to the foul
line and dribble it back.

134
00:08:31,211 --> 00:08:33,714
That's all I want you to do.

135
00:08:33,747 --> 00:08:35,616
Let's go.

136
00:08:35,649 --> 00:08:37,851
Yo, Father,
watch this.

137
00:08:40,353 --> 00:08:42,723
[ALL LAUGHING]
[CLEARS THROAT]

138
00:08:42,756 --> 00:08:45,092
Give me quiet
or give me laps.

139
00:08:45,125 --> 00:08:46,927
Pass it here.
But...

140
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,296
I've seen enough.
Just let me try it again.

141
00:08:49,329 --> 00:08:51,031
What is your name, son?

142
00:08:51,064 --> 00:08:52,833
Hank. Hank Gathers.

143
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:55,202
Okay, give me the ball,
go over there.

144
00:08:58,906 --> 00:08:59,973
Next.

145
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:01,709
Specs.

146
00:09:03,811 --> 00:09:06,313
I got them.
Man, you know
I do.

147
00:09:06,346 --> 00:09:11,118
Hank, all he wanted
us to do was dribble
up and back.

148
00:09:11,151 --> 00:09:13,253
So what's the big deal?

149
00:09:13,286 --> 00:09:15,589
You seem to be
the only one who
messed it up.

150
00:09:15,623 --> 00:09:18,258
Hey, man, I'm sure
I'm gonna be cut.

151
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:21,595
Me too.
Hey, Specs,

152
00:09:21,629 --> 00:09:24,131
you know, somebody's got to
ride the pipe

153
00:09:24,164 --> 00:09:26,133
or the starters get tired.

154
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:28,969
I don't remember Father Dave
mentioning a starting team.

155
00:09:29,002 --> 00:09:30,237
Figure it out, D,

156
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:34,207
it's gotta be you,
Raymond, Lorenzo,
me ans Douglas.

157
00:09:34,241 --> 00:09:36,877
Starting Derrick and Douglas
up front,

158
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:38,679
Lorenzo and Raymond at
the guards,

159
00:09:38,712 --> 00:09:39,980
and, Mike, you're at pivot.

160
00:09:41,314 --> 00:09:42,950
Ready...

161
00:09:44,284 --> 00:09:45,819
ALL: Break!

162
00:09:49,389 --> 00:09:51,124
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

163
00:09:53,894 --> 00:09:56,129
All right, you guys,
now don't bankrupt me.

164
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:59,199
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

165
00:10:08,809 --> 00:10:10,610
Are we feeling sorry
for ourselves?

166
00:10:11,344 --> 00:10:13,280
I'm better than most of them.

167
00:10:13,313 --> 00:10:16,083
No, you're not, Gathers,
you're just bigger.

168
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:18,886
I could take them all
one-on-one.

169
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:21,989
I, I got the moves,
Father Dave,
you know I do.

170
00:10:23,857 --> 00:10:26,960
What I know is you got
a couple of playground tricks.

171
00:10:26,994 --> 00:10:28,662
I don't play that game.

172
00:10:28,696 --> 00:10:33,433
In fact, you haven't shown me
anything except you got
a big mouth and a bad attitude.

173
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:36,003
All flash and no cash.

174
00:10:36,036 --> 00:10:39,873
All start and no finish.

175
00:10:39,907 --> 00:10:43,711
Don't you come moaning to me
about game time as long as you
gonna play that way.

176
00:10:45,212 --> 00:10:46,646
[SIGHS]

177
00:10:48,448 --> 00:10:52,352
I don't see why I have to go
to some stupid Catholic school
anyway?

178
00:10:52,385 --> 00:10:54,722
I hate it and
I hate Father Dave.

179
00:10:55,188 --> 00:10:56,423
Hank,

180
00:10:56,456 --> 00:10:58,391
I paid to see you
to St. Elizabeth's

181
00:10:58,425 --> 00:11:02,029
because it's the best chance
you have of making something
of yourself.

182
00:11:02,062 --> 00:11:04,164
Hank, you listen to me.

183
00:11:04,197 --> 00:11:08,301
Now, if I didn't think
you had it in you to do
all sorts of wonderful things,

184
00:11:08,335 --> 00:11:10,738
I wouldn't even bother.

185
00:11:10,771 --> 00:11:12,906
But I'm telling you, baby,
you're special.

186
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:16,744
You can do anything
in this world you want
to do.

187
00:11:16,777 --> 00:11:18,011
Tell that to Father Dave.

188
00:11:18,045 --> 00:11:19,246
No, you tell him.

189
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:20,347
Yeah, right.

190
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:22,850
Not in words, baby,
you show him.

191
00:11:22,883 --> 00:11:24,251
You prove him wrong.

192
00:11:24,284 --> 00:11:27,755
You show him that you are
as good as you think you are.

193
00:11:27,788 --> 00:11:31,191
You show the man that
he's a fool for not playing
you in those games.

194
00:11:31,224 --> 00:11:34,061
But you show him, baby.
Don't you tell him.

195
00:11:34,094 --> 00:11:35,695
You show him, okay?

196
00:11:36,463 --> 00:11:37,965
All right.

197
00:11:42,002 --> 00:11:43,871
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:12:09,429 --> 00:12:10,497
That was a great game.

199
00:12:10,530 --> 00:12:11,765
I did all the work.

200
00:12:24,177 --> 00:12:25,312
Get off me,
little punk.

201
00:12:25,345 --> 00:12:26,346
Punk?

202
00:12:32,485 --> 00:12:34,354
I'm gonna show
these guys how
to play.

203
00:12:41,561 --> 00:12:43,330
Yes! Yes!

204
00:12:47,868 --> 00:12:49,169
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

205
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:52,940
Ah, yeah. Ah, yeah.
Ah, yeah.

206
00:12:52,973 --> 00:12:55,075
All my free throws,
you know.

207
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:58,578
[ALL CHANTING] City champ!
City champ! City champ!

208
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:00,981
Okay, okay, okay.
Not yet, you're not.

209
00:13:01,014 --> 00:13:02,115
I know you've worked very hard

210
00:13:02,149 --> 00:13:03,817
but that's a tough team
down there.

211
00:13:03,851 --> 00:13:06,854
Father Dave, we're gonna
drop them guys like
a bad trans...

212
00:13:06,887 --> 00:13:08,088
All right.

213
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:11,058
Now, I'll feel very proud of you
as long as you play hard,

214
00:13:11,091 --> 00:13:13,393
and play like a team.

215
00:13:13,426 --> 00:13:15,295
Right? Having said that...

216
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:17,330
City what?

217
00:13:17,364 --> 00:13:19,332
ALL: City Champ!

218
00:13:19,366 --> 00:13:20,400
Get them!

219
00:13:21,234 --> 00:13:22,402
All right.

220
00:13:44,391 --> 00:13:46,359
FATHER DAVE: I don't care
that you lost,

221
00:13:48,095 --> 00:13:51,464
it's how you lost
that kills me.

222
00:13:51,498 --> 00:13:55,435
You played selfish,
and you played stupid.

223
00:13:57,037 --> 00:13:58,605
You didn't look like
a team out there,

224
00:13:58,638 --> 00:14:01,008
you looked like a street gang.

225
00:14:01,041 --> 00:14:02,109
Everything we talked about,

226
00:14:02,142 --> 00:14:05,078
everything that we worked on
went right out the window.

227
00:14:06,146 --> 00:14:08,381
Now, go on. Go on
and get dressed.
Go on.

228
00:14:11,618 --> 00:14:13,486
You talked hard
to those kids.

229
00:14:14,387 --> 00:14:15,588
Yes, ma'am, I did.

230
00:14:16,589 --> 00:14:18,191
You know, when I first heard
about you,

231
00:14:18,225 --> 00:14:23,263
I was a little suspicious
about what this white man
was doing living up here.

232
00:14:23,296 --> 00:14:25,198
Sometimes I wonder
myself.

233
00:14:25,232 --> 00:14:27,067
You get thrown out of
some place else?

234
00:14:28,301 --> 00:14:30,370
No, ma'am, I just left.

235
00:14:30,403 --> 00:14:32,305
Oh. And where might that be?

236
00:14:33,506 --> 00:14:35,108
Immaculate Heart.

237
00:14:36,309 --> 00:14:37,344
[CHUCKLES]

238
00:14:37,377 --> 00:14:40,613
You left there,
to come here?

239
00:14:40,647 --> 00:14:43,917
But then, honey, you must be
the stupidest white man
I ever seen.

240
00:14:43,951 --> 00:14:46,153
Here, honey,
Lucille Gathers.

241
00:14:46,186 --> 00:14:49,356
Mrs. Gathers, I'm very happy
to meet you.

242
00:14:49,389 --> 00:14:52,259
Those are both fine boys
that you have there.

243
00:14:52,292 --> 00:14:54,394
They're like night and day.
You know with Derrick,

244
00:14:54,427 --> 00:14:57,230
you always know
where you stand
'cause he's steady.

245
00:14:57,264 --> 00:14:58,631
But Hank,

246
00:14:58,665 --> 00:15:02,169
he's always trying to run
