01:21:17,373 --> 01:21:19,475
Get out of here.

1486
01:21:19,508 --> 01:21:21,044
I'm really proud
of you, Hank.

1487
01:21:23,079 --> 01:21:24,981
You know, Father Dave,

1488
01:21:25,014 --> 01:21:26,515
you've always been my hero.

1489
01:21:33,289 --> 01:21:34,423
[HORN TOOTING]

1490
01:21:34,457 --> 01:21:35,959
I'm coming.

1491
01:21:37,260 --> 01:21:38,327
I got to go.

1492
01:21:38,361 --> 01:21:40,129
Okay. Look, uh...

1493
01:21:40,163 --> 01:21:43,666
Derricks been talking
about us flying out
for the regional finals,

1494
01:21:43,699 --> 01:21:45,534
I mean, if you're still
in the tournament.

1495
01:21:45,568 --> 01:21:46,936
Well, we gonna make it
to the finals, mama.

1496
01:21:46,970 --> 01:21:50,639
So, you tell that buddy
go ahead and buy those
tickets. Non-refundable.

1497
01:21:50,673 --> 01:21:52,241
Come here, honey.

1498
01:21:54,010 --> 01:21:56,579
Look you be good, okay?
And you take care of yourself.

1499
01:21:56,612 --> 01:21:57,947
I will, mama.
You hear me?

1500
01:21:57,981 --> 01:21:59,648
I will.
I have to go.
Okay. All right.

1501
01:22:00,416 --> 01:22:01,617
Take care of yourself.

1502
01:22:01,650 --> 01:22:03,452
I will.

1503
01:22:03,486 --> 01:22:06,022
I love you.
I love you too, baby.

1504
01:22:06,055 --> 01:22:07,656
Tell Derrick to buy
those tickets, mama.

1505
01:22:09,325 --> 01:22:10,559
I love you.

1506
01:22:10,593 --> 01:22:12,061
HANK: I love you more.

1507
01:22:13,629 --> 01:22:15,031
[DOOR CLOSES]

1508
01:22:18,434 --> 01:22:20,403
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

1509
01:22:33,016 --> 01:22:35,351
And since Hank Gathers 
 returned the line-up,

1510
01:22:35,384 --> 01:22:38,187
the little engine you call 
 Loyola is ready and willing,

1511
01:22:38,221 --> 01:22:40,389
if not perhaps 100% able,

1512
01:22:40,423 --> 01:22:42,658
to make a run for 
 the national title.

1513
01:22:42,691 --> 01:22:45,761
But first they have to prove 
 themselves in regional action.

1514
01:22:45,794 --> 01:22:48,231
And tonight's semifinal game 
 versus Portland

1515
01:22:48,264 --> 01:22:50,433
should be an important test 
 for the Lions,

1516
01:22:50,466 --> 01:22:52,535
both physically 
 and psychologically.

1517
01:22:54,770 --> 01:22:56,539
Take it easy out there
tonight, Bank.

1518
01:22:57,540 --> 01:22:58,574
Why?

1519
01:22:58,607 --> 01:23:01,444
So you can get all
the headlines to
yourself again?

1520
01:23:01,477 --> 01:23:02,645
No, that's not it.

1521
01:23:04,313 --> 01:23:05,681
I'm worried about you.

1522
01:23:07,450 --> 01:23:09,785
Maybe I'm the only one
who see it,

1523
01:23:09,818 --> 01:23:13,256
but you're still not right.

1524
01:23:13,289 --> 01:23:15,324
You're still not playing
the way you used to.

1525
01:23:16,125 --> 01:23:18,361
[SCOFFS] What do you know, Bo?

1526
01:23:18,394 --> 01:23:20,496
You're just another
ignorant basketball player.

1527
01:23:20,529 --> 01:23:23,132
Then, it's perfect,
'cause that's just who
I am talking to.

1528
01:23:25,534 --> 01:23:27,336
It's like when
I tore up my knee.

1529
01:23:28,637 --> 01:23:30,306
This stuff happens, dude.

1530
01:23:32,175 --> 01:23:34,177
Even to lucky guys
like you and me.

1531
01:23:38,247 --> 01:23:40,015
Yeah, I heard that.

1532
01:23:41,850 --> 01:23:43,752
Be careful out there
tonight, Bank.

1533
01:23:45,788 --> 01:23:47,156
[SIGHS]

1534
01:23:47,190 --> 01:23:48,657
To get where we are

1535
01:23:48,691 --> 01:23:51,194
from where we came,

1536
01:23:51,227 --> 01:23:53,629
how much luck
do you think
we were owed?

1537
01:23:57,333 --> 01:23:58,667
[LAUGHING]

1538
01:24:02,805 --> 01:24:04,173
You know, Bo?

1539
01:24:04,207 --> 01:24:08,144
I think that's the most
words I've ever heard
you say at one time.

1540
01:24:08,611 --> 01:24:10,313
[LAUGHS]

1541
01:24:26,195 --> 01:24:27,430
Love you, man.

1542
01:24:28,364 --> 01:24:30,065
Thank you.
[SNIFFLES]

1543
01:24:31,734 --> 01:24:33,202
[GRUNTS]

1544
01:24:33,236 --> 01:24:34,570
Put me down, Hank.

1545
01:24:35,538 --> 01:24:37,173
Come on, man.
Let's go.

1546
01:24:40,476 --> 01:24:42,077
[CROWD CHEERING]

1547
01:24:43,712 --> 01:24:46,115
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

1548
01:25:01,730 --> 01:25:03,332
[EXCLAIMS]

1549
01:25:38,934 --> 01:25:40,469
Hank.

1550
01:25:58,554 --> 01:25:59,955
[MAMA SCREAMING]

1551
01:25:59,988 --> 01:26:02,691
Sweet Jesus, no!

1552
01:26:03,892 --> 01:26:05,361
[CRYING]

1553
01:26:08,997 --> 01:26:10,633
[CRYING] Father Dave,

1554
01:26:13,902 --> 01:26:15,404
Hank's gone.

1555
01:26:47,670 --> 01:26:49,338
Mama...

1556
01:26:59,748 --> 01:27:00,883
[CRYING]

1557
01:27:04,453 --> 01:27:05,788
Mama.

1558
01:27:16,064 --> 01:27:17,600
[CLEARS THROAT]

1559
01:27:25,441 --> 01:27:26,909
[SNIFFLES]

1560
01:27:26,942 --> 01:27:28,344
Everytime,

1561
01:27:29,378 --> 01:27:30,979
I pick up a basketball...

1562
01:27:34,617 --> 01:27:36,251
for the rest of my life...

1563
01:27:36,719 --> 01:27:37,920
[CRYING]

1564
01:27:39,888 --> 01:27:41,590
Hank Gathers will be with me.

1565
01:27:43,459 --> 01:27:44,993
Every jump shot...

1566
01:27:46,629 --> 01:27:48,897
[CRYING] every three pointer...

1567
01:27:52,668 --> 01:27:54,903
Hank is now part of me.

1568
01:27:56,071 --> 01:27:57,473
Hank,

1569
01:27:58,407 --> 01:27:59,708
was very happy when he left.

1570
01:28:02,010 --> 01:28:03,346
Very happy.

1571
01:28:07,049 --> 01:28:11,754
Hank would not have chosen
any other way, then the way
he left us.

1572
01:28:12,988 --> 01:28:14,823
On the basketball court.

1573
01:28:17,660 --> 01:28:19,728
I also know,

1574
01:28:19,762 --> 01:28:23,298
Hank you like to hear
one more cheer

1575
01:28:24,500 --> 01:28:29,438
from his fans, friends,
people who supported him.

1576
01:28:31,106 --> 01:28:32,941
One last applause

1577
01:28:34,410 --> 01:28:35,778
in his house.

1578
01:28:36,645 --> 01:28:38,614
[CROWD CLAPPING]

1579
01:29:09,712 --> 01:29:11,914
[CAPTIVATING MUSIC PLAYING]

1580
01:29:59,194 --> 01:30:00,896
Love you, man.

1581
01:30:01,697 --> 01:30:02,965
Thank you.

